  <summary>2/7/2001--Introduced.
Worker's Income Tax Credit Act of 2001 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an individual a limited (up to $350) tax credit equal to 6.2 percent of the sum of: (1) an individual's wages, salaries, tips, and other employee compensation includible in gross income; plus (2) the individual's earned income.</summary>
